reviews.review_text: Good times! Great show, great sound. Thanks for posting!
deer story to jack is sweet classic 78

Great show with a rippin' Frank's. Not sure why I forogt to review this when I downloaded. This is a great show, with the aawesome, insane Franklin's as the centerpiece. 

It's all about the '78 style: The guys all goin' nuts, trippin balls, yelling and singing crazy ways, playing tons of pwoer chords and everything loud and crashing. 

Play this one with some software reverb (www.un4seen.com). It's fuckin' awesome.

Seems a common way to go... Really like this show. Pretty cool that it has the SALT LAKE CITY sound check. I waited for years for them to break this cookie out.
Finally I am in the Military and I see the set list and they played it at of course SALT LAKE!
Anyway, the show itself is great. I really like Donna high up in the mix and you get that and some here.
Bob sounds like someone has a left hand Monkey wrench squeezing his balls every time he says 'thank you' between tunes. (NOT a tape speed issue)
The banter between songs is fun and loose.
Passenger is full tilt!
 Donna Jean hits those high notes in Passenger 
how anyone could not be blown away. 
This is the same woman who sang YOU Ain't   
woman ENOUGH in 1973. 
 Donna Jean if I could I would request nobody who bitches about you be allowed into the Promised Land...
And speaking of Bawdy, I am just trying to imagine what UTAH thought of Salt Lake City -that song is not exactly a Mormon recruitment tool.
Weir's 2nd joke was considerably less witty then the 1st one. Weir took his own 'long ago' advice about learning jokes to tell each other- to heart.
Donna gives us her best oh's and ah's for Candyman.
Brent great/ Woman SMARTER!
"BESIDES BRENT IS A DUDE"

Listen to how Donna and Bobby are jelling vocally during MUSIC. Pretty sweet!!!
Wow! tempo change towards the end of MUSIC .

2nd Set-Absolutely Monster FRANKLIN'S!
Keith making his own way?
 Garcia in a few spots switches lyrics
I am pretty sure he goes
"You plant FIRE, You are going to harvest wind"

 Donna/ Black Peter-"Come Around"
Jerry just goes off guitar wise kinda like he did MUSIC.
Hot Show!
Another Classic Betty Board "Another classic Betty Board!" Sound is rich and perfect. Betty really knows how to deliver the goods...
